    public static final String Eccl_2_19 = "And who knoweth whether he shall be a wise [man] or a fool? yet shall he have rule over all my labour wherein I have laboured, and wherein I have shewed myself wise under the sun. This [is] also vanity. ";
    public static final String Eccl_2_20 = "Therefore I went about to cause my heart to despair of all the labour which I took under the sun. ";
    public static final String Eccl_2_21 = "For there is a man whose labour [is] in wisdom, and in knowledge, and in equity; yet to a man that hath not laboured therein shall he leave it [for] his portion. This also [is] vanity and a great evil. ";
    public static final String Eccl_2_22 = "For what hath man of all his labour, and of the vexation of his heart, wherein he hath laboured under the sun? ";
    public static final String Eccl_2_23 = "For all his days [are] sorrows, and his travail grief; yea, his heart taketh not rest in the night. This is also vanity. ";
    public static final String Eccl_2_24 = "[There is] nothing better for a man, [than] that he should eat and drink, and [that] he should make his soul enjoy good in his labour. This also I saw, that it [was] from the hand of God. ";
