    public static final String Eccl_9_7 = "Go thy way, eat thy bread with joy, and drink thy wine with a merry heart; for God now accepteth thy works. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_8 = "Let thy garments be always white; and let thy head lack no ointment. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_9 = "Live joyfully with the wife whom thou lovest all the days of the life of thy vanity, which he hath given thee under the sun, all the days of thy vanity: for that [is] thy portion in [this] life, and in thy labour which thou takest under the sun. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_10 = "Whatsoever thy hand findeth to do, do [it] with thy might; for [there is] no work, nor device, nor knowledge, nor wisdom, in the grave, whither thou goest. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_11 = "I returned, and saw under the sun, that the race [is] not to the swift, nor the battle to the strong, neither yet bread to the wise, nor yet riches to men of understanding, nor yet favour to men of skill; but time and chance happeneth to them all. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_12 = "For man also knoweth not his time: as the fishes that are taken in an evil net, and as the birds that are caught in the snare; so [are] the sons of men snared in an evil time, when it falleth suddenly upon them. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_13 = "This wisdom have I seen also under the sun, and it [seemed] great unto me: ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_14 = "[There was] a little city, and few men within it; and there came a great king against it, and besieged it, and built great bulwarks against it: ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_15 = "Now there was found in it a poor wise man, and he by his wisdom delivered the city; yet no man remembered that same poor man. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_16 = "Then said I, Wisdom [is] better than strength: nevertheless the poor man's wisdom [is] despised, and his words are not heard. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_17 = "The words of wise [men are] heard in quiet more than the cry of him that ruleth among fools. ";
    public static final String Eccl_9_18 = "Wisdom [is] better than weapons of war: but one sinner destroyeth much good. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_1 = "Dead flies cause the ointment of the apothecary to send forth a stinking savour: [so doth] a little folly him that is in reputation for wisdom [and] honour. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_2 = "A wise man's heart [is] at his right hand; but a fool's heart at his left. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_3 = "Yea also, when he that is a fool walketh by the way, his wisdom faileth [him,] and he saith to every one [that] he [is] a fool. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_4 = "If the spirit of the ruler rise up against thee, leave not thy place; for yielding pacifieth great offences. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_5 = "There is an evil [which] I have seen under the sun, as an error [which] proceedeth from the ruler: ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_6 = "Folly is set in great dignity, and the rich sit in low place. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_7 = "I have seen servants upon horses, and princes walking as servants upon the earth. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_8 = "He that diggeth a pit shall fall into it; and whoso breaketh an hedge, a serpent shall bite him. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_9 = "Whoso removeth stones shall be hurt therewith; [and] he that cleaveth wood shall be endangered thereby. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_10 = "If the iron be blunt, and he do not whet the edge, then must he put to more strength: but wisdom [is] profitable to direct. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_11 = "Surely the serpent will bite without enchantment; and a babbler is no better. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_12 = "The words of a wise man's mouth [are] gracious; but the lips of a fool will swallow up himself. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_13 = "The beginning of the words of his mouth [is] foolishness: and the end of his talk [is] mischievous madness. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_14 = "A fool also is full of words: a man cannot tell what shall be; and what shall be after him, who can tell him? ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_15 = "The labour of the foolish wearieth every one of them, because he knoweth not how to go to the city. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_16 = "Woe to thee, O land, when thy king [is] a child, and thy princes eat in the morning! ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_17 = "Blessed [art] thou, O land, when thy king [is] the son of nobles, and thy princes eat in due season, for strength, and not for drunkenness! ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_18 = "By much slothfulness the building decayeth; and through idleness of the hands the house droppeth through. ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_19 = "A feast is made for laughter, and wine maketh merry: but money answereth all [things.] ";
    public static final String Eccl_10_20 = "Curse not the king, no not in thy thought; and curse not the rich in thy bedchamber: for a bird of the air shall carry the voice, and that which hath wings shall tell the matter. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_1 = "Cast thy bread upon the waters: for thou shalt find it after many days. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_2 = "Give a portion to seven, and also to eight; for thou knowest not what evil shall be upon the earth. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_3 = "If the clouds be full of rain, they empty [themselves] upon the earth: and if the tree fall toward the south, or toward the north, in the place where the tree falleth, there it shall be. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_4 = "He that observeth the wind shall not sow; and he that regardeth the clouds shall not reap. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_5 = "As thou knowest not what [is] the way of the spirit, [nor] how the bones [do grow] in the womb of her that is with child: even so thou knowest not the works of God who maketh all. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_6 = "In the morning sow thy seed, and in the evening withhold not thine hand: for thou knowest not whether shall prosper, either this or that, or whether they both [shall be] alike good. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_7 = "Truly the light [is] sweet, and a pleasant [thing it is] for the eyes to behold the sun: ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_8 = "But if a man live many years, [and] rejoice in them all; yet let him remember the days of darkness; for they shall be many. All that cometh [is] vanity. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_9 = "Rejoice, O young man, in thy youth; and let thy heart cheer thee in the days of thy youth, and walk in the ways of thine heart, and in the sight of thine eyes: but know thou, that for all these [things] God will bring thee into judgment. ";
    public static final String Eccl_11_10 = "Therefore remove sorrow from thy heart, and put away evil from thy flesh: for childhood and youth [are] vanity. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_1 = "Remember now thy Creator in the days of thy youth, while the evil days come not, nor the years draw nigh, when thou shalt say, I have no pleasure in them; ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_2 = "While the sun, or the light, or the moon, or the stars, be not darkened, nor the clouds return after the rain: ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_3 = "In the day when the keepers of the house shall tremble, and the strong men shall bow themselves, and the grinders cease because they are few, and those that look out of the windows be darkened, ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_4 = "And the doors shall be shut in the streets, when the sound of the grinding is low, and he shall rise up at the voice of the bird, and all the daughters of musick shall be brought low; ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_5 = "Also [when] they shall be afraid of [that which is] high, and fears [shall be] in the way, and the almond tree shall flourish, and the grasshopper shall be a burden, and desire shall fail: because man goeth to his long home, and the mourners go about the streets: ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_6 = "Or ever the silver cord be loosed, or the golden bowl be broken, or the pitcher be broken at the fountain, or the wheel broken at the cistern. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_7 = "Then shall the dust return to the earth as it was: and the spirit shall return unto God who gave it. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_8 = "Vanity of vanities, saith the preacher; all [is] vanity. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_9 = "And moreover, because the preacher was wise, he still taught the people knowledge; yea, he gave good heed, and sought out, [and] set in order many proverbs. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_10 = "The preacher sought to find out acceptable words: and [that which was] written [was] upright, [even] words of truth. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_11 = "The words of the wise [are] as goads, and as nails fastened by the masters of assemblies, [which] are given from one shepherd. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_12 = "And further, by these, my son, be admonished: of making many books [there is] no end; and much study [is] a weariness of the flesh. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_13 = "Let us hear the conclusion of the whole matter: Fear God, and keep his commandments: for this [is] the whole [duty] of man. ";
    public static final String Eccl_12_14 = "For God shall bring every work into judgment, with every secret thing, whether [it be] good, or whether [it be] evil. ";
